Luba Katz (2003)

CDS region: mean
Species: 28 sp., 3 domains (incl. human)
Resolution: species, domain

* Negative mid-CDS [C] in bacteria and some archaea and eukaryotes.

* 1 blue bacteria (Synechocystis PCC6803). This is not consistent with our results (possible due to different shuffling)

* dLFE not correlated with CAI


Evidence for selection:
1) dLFE found using dinucleotide-preserving shuffling.
2) stronger dLFE in bacterial polycistronic bacterial genes
3) stronger dLFE in s. cervisiae genes containing introns

Evidence for CDS mRNA interactions:

"Additionally, a stem-loop in the coding sequence of the yeast ASH1 gene can localize ASH1 mRNA to the bud tip" (Chartrand et al. 1999).

"secondary structure in ORFs can interfere with translation" (Klionsky et al. 1986; Guisez et al. 1993; Schmittgen et al. 1994).

